    </p>

    <p>
      I try to practice <a href="/blog/stack-selection">tech stack obsession</a
      >.
    </p>

    <h3>About This Blog</h3>

    <p>
      To that end, I built this blog template using <a
        href="https://astro.build/">astro.build</a
      > and <a href="http://picocss.com/">Pico CSS</a>. I co-run the keep it
      simple community (400+ members), run an online book club, and record the
      "pages of my life" podcast (5.8k+ listeners).
    </p>

    <p>
      I play a good deal of <a href="/blog/stack-selection">RSS hunt</a> in the digital
      realm, keep trying to <a href="/blog/stack-selection">keep it simple</a>,
      and love to
      <a href="/blog/stack-selection">avoid writing CSS.</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      I hope that my <a href="/blog/stack-selection">writings</a> become cited in
      the
      <a href="https://astro.build/themes">Astro Theme Library</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      I hope you connect with me on
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-khami-5a0a7a135/"
        >LinkedIn</a
      > (5k+ subscribers),
      <a href="https://x.com/skeptrune">X</a> (1.3k+ followers),
      <a href="http://github.com/skeptrunedev">Github</a> (100+ followers), or over
      <a href="mailto:me@skeptrune.io">email</a>.
    </p>

    <h3>Chatting and Crowdsourcing</h3>

    <p>
      I absolutely love to exchange ideas. If you ever want to brainstorm,
      <a href="https://cal.com/nick.k">here's a little page</a> to help me out with
      scheduling.
    </p>

    <p>
      I go out of my way to chat with folks who build in public or contribute to
      open source. I love to hear about other people's projects and experiences.
      I also love to hear about your favorite tools and how you use them.
    </p>
  </article>
</SimpleLayout>
